timeline.message: Support for checking partition key filter coverage

timeline.bodyText:
We usually keep the type from getter method consistent to the setter method.
What about return String here and do the JSON parse in WarnOnScanWithoutPartitionPredicate ?
timeline.author: wenleix

replies.bodyText:
Having a List<List<>> for configuration looks too complicated ..
As discussed offline, let's focus on simple use case. The semantic can be:
Here is a list of common partitioned columns.  If the table is partitioned on any of these columns, 
we expect the query need to have filter on at least one of those partitioned columns.

And in most companies in Bay Area, this will just be set to [ds] .
replies.author: wenleix

timeline.bodyText:
nit: I think we usually do toImmutableList() and toImmutableSet() whenever feasible.
Also I personally prefer to put new lines for stream APIs, e.g.
            List<String> partitionKey = tableHandle.getPartitionColumns().stream()
                    .map(HiveColumnHandle::getName)
                    .collect(toImmutableList());
timeline.author: wenleix

replies.bodyText: Actually I think we don't need this partitionKey anymore (we can directly compute relevantColumns )
replies.author: wenleix

timeline.author: wenleix

timeline.bodyText:
Note Hive partition is not a "partitioning" at engine level. Presto engine "partitioning" corresponds to Hive bucket.  Hive partition filter is modeled as table layout selection in Presto today :(
What about TableLayoutFilterCoverage?  cc @rschlussel

replies.bodyText: Does table layout mean anything at all to the end user? I think that is mixing up implementation details with user visible concepts?

timeline.bodyText: nit: I am not a big fan of Yoda conditions.
timeline.author: wenleix

timeline.bodyText: nit: This line's getting long. it's probably about time to split this into one line per-argument.
timeline.author: rschlussel

timeline.bodyText:
hmm... this basically says "the table is not partitioned; or it's not partitioned on known columns (e.g. ds)".
Returning UNKNOWN for this is a bit weird. Because we know there is no violation / concern for sure. But I also don't have a good suggestions.
See if @rschlussel has any thought about how the enum values in PartitioningFilterCoverage should be . Otherwise, I am fine to keep it as is :)
timeline.author: wenleix

replies.bodyText:
Unknown is pulling double duty as both unknown (not implemented by the connector) and not applicable (we know it's fine).
We could add a fourth value, the question is does that make the API easier to consume when there is nothing that leverages the distinction between unknown and not applicable.
replies.author: aweisberg
